By: Delegate Pena–Melnyk Delegates Pena–Melnyk, Bagnall, D. Jones, Spiegel,
Rose, Alston, Cullison, Guzzone, Hill, Hutchinson, S. Johnson, Kaufman,
Kipke, Lopez, Martinez, M. Morgan, Reilly, Rosenberg, Ross, Taveras,
White Holland, and Woorman
Introduced and read first time: February 13, 2026
Assigned to: Health
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 3, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Health Occupations and, Public Health, and Insurance – Menopause – Provider
3 Training and Coverage Requirements, Policy Initiatives, and Access to Care
4 FOR the purpose of altering the membership of the State Advisory Council on Health and
5 Wellness; requiring health occupations boards that require licensees or certificate
6 holders to complete certain continuing education to grant a certain number of hours
7 for every hour of continuing education for menopause and menopause–associated
8 symptoms; authorizing certain health occupations boards to establish a maximum
9 number of certain continuing education credits granted; requiring the Department
10 to identify a certain training program in consultation with certain professional
11 associations; requiring certain insurers, nonprofit health service plans, and health
12 maintenance organizations to provide coverage for the evaluation and management
13 of menopause and menopause–associated conditions; requiring the Maryland
14 Commission for Women and the Maryland Department of Health to take certain
15 actions related to perimenopausal, menopausal, and postmenopausal conditions; and
16 generally relating to provider training and, health insurance coverage, policy
17 initiatives, and access to care related to menopause.
18 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
19 Article – Health – General
20 Section 13–201
21 Annotated Code of Maryland
